  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pacemaker requirement in the immediate post procedure phase following TAVI is approximately
      20% depending on device type and patient characteristics. There is a signal from recent
      studies suggesting increased risk of sudden cardiac / unexplained death in the first 30-60
      days. This study aims to address whether there is a mortality advantage to having a pacemaker
      in the short term
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
